cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new regularization technique for deep neural networks. It may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with neural networks. Additionally, the experiments conducted on image datasets suggest that it may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) as these sub-categories often deal with image classification tasks. Finally, it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as deep neural networks are a popular tool in AI research.
